cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR

Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of vSLAM, which is a topic in robotics and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses post-processing techniques applied to sparse 3D point-cloud maps, which is a topic in computer vision. Hence, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely category. The paper evaluates different combinations of algorithms for outlier removal and upsampling, which is a topic in machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper deals with the conversion of a point-cloud map to a 3D voxel grid potentially suitable for path planning, which is a topic in graphics. Hence, cs.GR (Graphics) is also a likely category.
